Cafe with a view? Say less 😍✨
Just 15 minutes from Patong Beach, Cafe Phuket Viewpoint is a hidden gem that gives you a piano by the sea, views that steal your breath, and food that hits the soul.
From pink florals and chill cocktails to the sound of waves crashing — this one’s an actual dream 🫶

📍Location: “Cafe Phuket Viewpoint, Thailand” 

Good vibes, even better company, and shrimp curry worth walking miles for 🍤🌊
Definitely adding this to my must-visit list again!

If you’re in Phuket and looking for the ultimate nightlife experience, these 3 clubs are where the real party begins✨🥂🤌

We started the night at Illuzion, one of the top 100 clubs in the world. Massive LED walls, live international DJs, insane sound systems, and aerial performances—this place feels like a Vegas-style nightclub right in the heart of Patong’s Bangla Road. The vibe? Electric⚡️💫

Next stop was Armania—this one’s more underrated but definitely a hidden gem. It’s chic, stylish, and the crowd is international. Music shifts between commercial house, EDM, and live acts. The vibe is classy but fun, with some serious dance floor energy.

We wrapped the night at Sugar Club, Phuket’s hub for all things hip-hop, Afrobeat, and R&B. If you’re into dancing, bottle service, and a wild-but-safe party crowd, this is where you end your night. The dancers and themed nights keep things fresh every time.

Each club offers a different vibe but together, they make up the must-do trio of Phuket nightlife.
Free entries most nights, great drink deals, and VIP tables if you’re feeling fancy.

Trust me—Bangla Road isn’t just hype. It’s an experience.
